# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env

# Build output
/_output/
/chok
/chok-dev

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/

# Runtime artefacts produced by example apps / local smoke runs.
# Each example uses SQLite by default and lumberjack-rotated log
# files; these are local-only state, must never enter the tree.
# The `examples/` directory itself stays version-controlled.
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
examples/**/logs/
examples/**/cache/

# macOS Finder droppings
.DS_Store

# Local-only planning / scratch space. Anything inside .private/ is
# considered intentionally outside the public history — internal
# design drafts, agent SPECs, ad-hoc notes. Use docs/ for anything
# meant to ship to readers.
.private/
